<paragraph id="8B8536C2E50F927D43B9A5E8DB8B36DD" blockId="20.[138,392,1255,1279]" box="[138,392,1255,1279]" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D43B9A5E8DB8B36DD" box="[138,392,1255,1279]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Comparative discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8536C2E50F927D43B9A417DACD3790" blockId="20.[138,1185,1304,1685]" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">
In particular, this species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D4131A417D8723712" authorityName="Girard" authorityYear="1850" box="[514,625,1304,1328]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D4131A417D8723712" box="[514,625,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Procerodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a well-developed penial papilla provided with a thick zone of circular muscle (
<figureCitation id="13012A47E50F927D407BA437D9CA3772" box="[840,969,1336,1360]" captionStart="Figures 28–30" captionStartId="20.[138,207,1113,1132]" captionTargetBox="[191,1130,133,1075]" captionTargetId="figure-150@20.[191,1132,133,1077]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 28–30. Procerodes plebeius and Uteriporus pacificus? (28) P. plebeius, V.Pl. 954.2, photomicrograph of penial papilla. (29) U. pacificus?, sagittal reconstruction of the copulatory apparatus (from Poljakova, 1991: figure 15B; labels adapted according to current terminology). (30) U. pacificus, specimen BC 7-5 (ZMA), photomicrograph of horizontal section of the receptacular duct; anterior to the left." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221483/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Figure 28</figureCitation>
). The species 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D47BBA436DADE3753" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="plebeius">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D47BBA436DADE3753" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">P. plebeius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D4244A456D8A33753" authority="Wilhelmi, 1909" authorityName="Wilhelmi" authorityYear="1909" box="[375,672,1369,1393]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="dohrni">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D4244A456DBDC3753" box="[375,479,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">P. dohrni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB4B33E50F927D42D4A456D8A33753" author="Wilhelmi J" box="[487,672,1369,1393]" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" refId="ref9500" refString="Wilhelmi J. 1909. Tricladen, Fauna und Flora des Golfes von Neapel. 32, Berlin: R. Friedlander und Sohn. xii + 405 p, 16 pls." type="book" year="1909">Wilhelmi, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which also exhibits a thick zone of circular muscle on the penial papilla, by the presence of a copulatory bursa that is absent in the latter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8536C2E50F927D4396A4B4DB4E34B7" blockId="20.[138,1185,1304,1685]" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">
The present record for 
<collectingCountry id="F32D7652E50F927D42F7A4B4D81A37F1" box="[452,537,1467,1491]" name="Iceland" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Iceland</collectingCountry>
considerably extends the known range of the species since thus far it had been reported from Cephalonia, Crete, Black Sea and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F32D7652E50F927D43B9A4F4DAED3431" box="[138,238,1531,1555]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">England</collectingCountry>
, where it was found in brackish habitats. In 
<collectingCountry id="F32D7652E50F927D4024A4F4D9733431" box="[791,880,1531,1555]" name="Iceland" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Iceland</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D40B3A4F3D9FB3431" box="[896,1016,1531,1555]" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="plebeius">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D40B3A4F3D9FB3431" box="[896,1016,1531,1555]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">P. plebeius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from the extreme upper littoral, in coarse sand. At the same locality 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D4713A713DB3B3476" authority="(Strom, 1768)" baseAuthorityName="Strom" baseAuthorityYear="1768" family="Procerodidae" genus="Procerodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="littoralis">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D4713A713DEA33416" box="[1056,1184,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">P. littoralis</emphasis>
(Ström, 1768)
</taxonomicName>
was present, albeit on 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A4D41E50F927D415FA732D8DC3476" box="[620,735,1596,1620]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Fucaceae" genus="Fucus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B94EEAD0E50F927D415FA732D8AF3476" box="[620,684,1597,1620]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Fucus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, a species of marine triclad that is also known to occur in brackish localities and that was already known from 
<collectingCountry id="F32D7652E50F927D477FA752DEA23457" box="[1100,1185,1629,1653]" name="Iceland" pageId="20" pageNumber="463">Iceland</collectingCountry>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB4B33E50F927D4389A772DB4334B7" author="Sluys R" box="[186,320,1661,1685]" pageId="20" pageNumber="463" refId="ref9110" refString="Sluys R. 1989. A Monograph of the Marine Triclads. Rotterdam and Brookfield: A. A. Balkema. XII + 463 p." type="book" year="1989">Sluys 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
